1."docker version" 
2."docker --version"

Install images
Docker pull "image name" (ex hello world)

List Installed Images
"docker images"

List Docker Containers
"docker ps -a"

Run Image in Docker
"docker run image name"

displays the summary of the amount of disk space used by the docker daemon
"df -h"

Changes root disk space to 5gb or the desired space
"Docker run -it --name cent3 --storage-opt size=5G centos"

Lists containers-ID-Name-Limits-Usage
"Docker stats"

Inspect any image docker(prived full details about the selected image)
"Docker inspect centos:latest"
